## Round 3 update (2026-05-22)

ClawSweeper round 3 (15:38 UTC) flagged two more defects after rounds 1 and 2 closed. Both held under Locke's verification and are fixed on this branch.

### Fix 4 — Add `cron_*` family to `CORE_TOOL_DEFINITIONS` (catalog/profile gap)

Without this, the default `coding` profile and the `openclaw` tool group are both built from `CORE_TOOL_DEFINITIONS` via `listCoreToolIdsForProfile` + `buildCoreToolGroupMap`. Since the nine per-action `cron_*` ids were missing from the catalog, `filterToolsByPolicy` dropped them as "not in the active profile's allowlist." Default-profile users (the common case) never saw the per-action tools and continued to hit the legacy super-tool — negating the value of the fix for everyone except hand-tuned configs.

`src/agents/tool-catalog.ts`: added nine entries mirroring the legacy `cron` entry's `sectionId: "automation"`, `profiles: ["coding"]`, `includeInOpenClawGroup: true`.

### Fix 5 — `cron` deny/allow expands to cover the `cron_*` family across every policy path

Without this, the matcher in `src/agents/tool-policy-match.ts` is shared by all paths (global, per-agent, group, sender, sandbox, inherited, subagent) and only matches `cron` exactly. A user config like `tools.deny: ["cron"]` would block the legacy super-tool while leaving `cron_update`, `cron_remove`, etc open in every non-subagent session. Round 2's fix was scoped to `SUBAGENT_TOOL_DENY_ALWAYS` only.

`src/agents/tool-policy-shared.ts`: added a `TOOL_FAMILY_ALIASES` map inside `expandToolGroups` so a literal `"cron"` entry expands to `["cron", "cron_*"]`. Every consumer routes through `expandToolGroups` + `compileGlobPatterns`, so the change covers all policy paths in one place. Existing user configs stay safe — `"cron"` keeps matching the legacy tool and now implicitly covers the per-action decomposition.

